stock pen
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a small utility yard for keeping animals in a restricted space either to tame or to treat an injury or illness.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Includes fat stock pens.
